This paper is about neural text generation, which is a subfield of natural language processing (NLP). The paper proposes a new algorithm for beam search, which is a common technique used in NLP. Therefore, cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely sub-category. 

The paper also involves optimization and machine learning, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). 

Additionally, the paper mentions image captioning, which falls under cs.CV (Computer Vision). Finally, the paper's use of neural networks suggests that it could also belong to cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
